   573→### 5.3 Frustum Culling
   574→
   575→**File:** `apps/canvas/src/canvas/layers/MicroLayer.tsx:62-83`
   576→
   577→```typescript
   578→function filterVisibleTasks(tasks: TaskRender[], viewportBounds?: ViewportBounds): TaskRender[] {
   579→  if (!viewportBounds) return tasks;
   580→
   581→  const padding = 100; // Render slightly outside for smooth panning
   582→  const minX = viewportBounds.minX - padding;
   583→  const maxX = viewportBounds.maxX + padding;
   584→  const minY = viewportBounds.minY - padding;
   585→  const maxY = viewportBounds.maxY + padding;
   586→
   587→  return tasks.filter((task) => {
   588→    const taskStartX = task.startDay * pxPerDay;
   589→    const taskEndX = taskStartX + task.duration * pxPerDay;
   590→    const taskY = -task.trainIndex * pxPerTrain - pxPerTrain / 2;
   591→
   592→    const xOverlap = taskEndX >= minX && taskStartX <= maxX;
   593→    const yOverlap = taskY + pxPerTrain / 2 >= minY && taskY - pxPerTrain / 2 <= maxY;
   594→
   595→    return xOverlap && yOverlap;
   596→  });
   597→}
   598→```
   599→
   600→### VERIFICATION: VERIFIED
   601→- RBush queries are <0.5ms for 60k items
   602→- TypedArray storage is ~10x more memory efficient than objects
   603→- Frustum culling limits HTML labels to visible viewport + padding
   604→
   605→### CRITICAL MIGRATION NOTES
   606→1. Bulk load is faster than individual inserts for RBush
   607→2. Cursor pattern avoids allocations in hot paths
   608→3. Always add padding to frustum culling for smooth panning
   609→4. TypedArray SoA pattern is essential for >50k entities
