## 6. Memory Management Insights

### GC is the Primary Bottleneck

From state management research:
> "The primary bottleneck in WebGL applications is Garbage Collection, not rendering."

### Structure of Arrays (SoA) Pattern

```typescript
// BAD: Array of Structures (60k objects = 60k GC-tracked allocations)
const tasks = [
  { id: 'T1', x: 0, y: 0, width: 10, type: 'maintenance' },
  // ... 60,000 more objects
];

// GOOD: Structure of Arrays (~1.2MB in TypedArrays)
const taskStore = {
  count: 60000,
  x: new Float32Array(60000),
  y: new Float32Array(60000),
  width: new Float32Array(60000),
  type: new Uint8Array(60000),
  flags: new Uint8Array(60000),
};
```

### Object Pooling

```typescript
class VectorPool {
  private pool: Vector3[] = [];
  private index = 0;

  acquire(): Vector3 {
    const vec = this.pool[this.index];
    this.index = (this.index + 1) % this.pool.length;
    return vec;  // No allocation!
  }

  reset() {
    this.index = 0;
  }
}
```

