## 3. deck.gl Comparison

### deck.gl Overview

deck.gl is a WebGL2/WebGPU visualization framework optimized for large-scale data visualization.

**Performance envelope:**
- ~1M data items at 60 FPS on 2015 MacBook Pro
- Performance degrades significantly approaching 10M items
- Browser memory limits practical usage to 10M-100M without chunking

**Source:** [deck.gl Performance Optimization](https://deck.gl/docs/developer-guide/performance)

### OrthographicView for 2D

OrthographicView is designed for non-geospatial 2D visualization:

```javascript
import { OrthographicView } from '@deck.gl/core';

const view = new OrthographicView({
  controller: true,
  flipY: true // top-left coordinates
});

// View state
